Ethiopia, officially known as the Federal Democratic Republic of Ethiopia, is a sovereign state located in the Horn of [[Africa, community action for sustainability|Africa]]. With over 100 million inhabitants, Ethiopia is the most populous landlocked country in the world, as well as the second-most populous nation on the African continent after [[Nigeria]]. Its capital and largest city is Addis Ababa. {{W|Ethiopia}}

== Environmental issues ==

As in many neighboring countries, most environmental issues in Ethiopia relate to deforestation and endangered species. {{W|Environmental issues in Ethiopia}}

